# MustangMeals 🐴

Rate and review food spots on the Cal Poly SLO campus.

---

## Local Development

### 1. Install Node.js
Download from https://nodejs.org (LTS version)

### 2. Install Expo CLI + EAS CLI
```bash
npm install -g expo-cli eas-cli
```

### 3. Install dependencies
```bash
cd MustangMeals
npm install
```

### 4. Start the app
```bash
npx expo start
```

Scan the QR code with **Expo Go** on your phone to preview instantly.

---

## Publishing to App Store + Google Play

### Step 1 — Create your accounts (do this first)

| Store | URL | Cost |
|---|---|---|
| Apple App Store | https://developer.apple.com/programs | $99/year |
| Google Play Store | https://play.google.com/console | $25 one-time |

---

### Step 2 — Set up EAS

```bash
# Log in to your Expo account (create one free at expo.dev)
eas login

# Link this project to EAS (run inside the MustangMeals folder)
eas init

# This gives you a projectId — paste it into app.json under extra.eas.projectId
```

---

### Step 3 — Fill in your credentials in eas.json

Open `eas.json` and replace the placeholder values:

| Placeholder | Where to find it |
|---|---|
| `YOUR_APPLE_ID@email.com` | Your Apple Developer login email |
| `YOUR_APP_STORE_CONNECT_APP_ID` | App Store Connect → My Apps → your app → App Information |
| `YOUR_APPLE_TEAM_ID` | https://developer.apple.com → Membership → Team ID |
| `google-service-account.json` | Google Play Console → Setup → API access → Service accounts |

---

### Step 4 — Create your app icon + splash screen

Place these files in the `assets/` folder:

| File | Size | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `icon.png` | 1024×1024 | No transparency, no rounded corners (stores handle that) |
| `splash.png` | 1284×2778 | Your logo centered, white background |
| `adaptive-icon.png` | 1024×1024 | Android only — can have transparency |
| `favicon.png` | 48×48 | Web only |

Free tool to generate all sizes: https://www.appicon.co

---

### Step 5 — Build for both stores

```bash
# Build for both iOS and Android at once (runs in Expo's cloud)
npm run build:all

# Or individually:
npm run build:ios
npm run build:android
```

This uploads your code to Expo's servers and builds the `.ipa` and `.aab` files.
You'll get a download link when done (takes ~10–20 min).

---

### Step 6 — Submit to the stores

```bash
# Submit to both stores automatically
npm run submit:ios
npm run submit:android
```

Or download the build files and upload manually via App Store Connect / Google Play Console.

---

### Step 7 — Store listings

Before your app goes live, each store needs:

**Both stores:**
- App name: MustangMeals
- Short description: Rate and review food spots at Cal Poly SLO
- Screenshots: at least 3 (use the Expo Go simulator)
- Privacy policy URL: required — generate one free at https://privacypolicygenerator.info

**Apple only:**
- Age rating (choose 4+)
- Category: Food & Drink

**Android only:**
- Content rating questionnaire (5 min in Play Console)

---

## Review Timeline

| Store | Typical Wait |
|---|---|
| Google Play | 1–3 days |
| Apple App Store | 1–7 days |

